        "avatar_template": "https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/t/6f9a4e/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-04-29T20:21:53.287Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>After losing another cluster to negligence it\u2019s time to setup archiving. I have couple of questions.</p>\n<p><strong>1. Is there a way to setup backups directly from the config?</strong></p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">[backup_agent]\ncommand = /usr/lib/foundationdb/backup_agent/backup_agent\nlogdir = /var/log/foundationdb\n\n[backup_agent.1]\n</code></pre>\n<p>Can I add <code>datadir = /backups/</code> for the backup agent or something similar? I understand I can run the command <code>fdbbackup start -d  /backups</code> afterward but was curious if this step can done via config.</p>\n<p><strong>2. How many backup agents are reasonable?</strong><br>\nI have 8 CPU server with 2TB NVME as data store and 2TB normal HDD. I want to point backups to the normal HDD.</p>\n<p>I used 4 agents, but I made the selection quite arbitrary</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">[backup_agent.1]\n[backup_agent.2]\n[backup_agent.3]\n[backup_agent.4]\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>3. Any tweaks or suggestions?</strong><br>\nWant to make sure the backups are close as possible to the current state of cluster so if something  happens we can recover quickly.</p>\n<p>Any pointers are appreciated.</p>",
